{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the 'rawcontinue' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for 'continue' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"5968156":{"pageid":5968156,"ns":0,"title":"Needle (comics)","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"{{Superherobox| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics-->\n| image = [[Image:Spider Woman 1978 Issue 9.jpg|250px]]\n| caption = The Needle<br />Pencils by [[Carmine Infantino]]\n| comic_color = background:#ff8080\n| character_name = Needle\n| publisher = [[Marvel Comics]]\n| debut = ''[[Spider-Woman]]'' #9 (Dec 1978)\n| creators = [[Mark Gruenwald]]<br />[[Carmine Infantino]]<br />[[Al Gordon (comics)|Al Gordon]]\n| alliance_color = background:#c0c0ff\n| real_name = Josef Saint <ref>Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe A to Z Update #02 (2010)</ref>\n|species=[[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|Human Mutant]]\n| alliances = [[Night Shift (comics)|Night Shift]]\n| aliases = \n| powers = Ability to paralyze his foes with his one good eye<br> Stronger and more spry than a typical man his age<br>Wields a yard long needle.\n}}\n\nThe '''Needle''' is a [[comic book]] [[Character (arts)|character]]. He is a [[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|mutant]] [[supervillain]] in [[Marvel Comics]]' main [[Shared universe|shared]] [[Marvel Universe|universe]]. Created by [[Mark Gruenwald]], [[Carmine Infantino]], and [[Al Gordon (comics)|Al Gordon]],{{cn|date=February 2013}} the character first appeared in ''[[Spider-Woman]]'' #9 (December 1978).\n\n==Publication history==\nThe character's origin was recounted in his debut appearance in ''Spider-Woman'' #9.\n\nCreator [[Mark Gruenwald]] brought the character back during his run on the ''[[West Coast Avengers]]'' as a member of the villain team [[Night Shift (comics)|Night Shift]], which included other former Spider-Woman foes.\n\n==Fictional character biography==\nAfter being mugged one night while leaving work, Josef Saint, an elderly tailor, lost an eye and his ability to speak. While recuperating, he discovered that he has the power to paralyze with his gaze. Seeking revenge, Saint assumed the guise of the vigilante the '''Needle'''. Armed with a yard-long needle, the mute villain attacked young men on the streets at night, sewing their mouths shut. After victimizing [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agent Jerry Hunt, the Needle incurred the wrath of [[Spider-Woman (Jessica Drew)|Spider-Woman]], the agent's girlfriend, and she took him out with a close-range venom blast. He was subsequently arrested.<ref>''Spider-Woman'' #9</ref>\n\nWith other superhuman adventurers and criminals, the Needle was imprisoned by the [[Locksmith (comics)|Locksmith]], but then freed by Spider-Woman.<ref>''Spider-Woman'' #50</ref>\n\nThe Needle joined the [[Night Shift (comics)|Night Shift]], and teamed with [[Captain America]] against the [[Power Broker]] and his augmented mutates.<ref>''Captain America'' #330-331</ref> Alongside the Night Shift, he tested [[Moon Knight]] to take over as the leader of the Night Shift.<ref>''Solo Avengers'' #3</ref> Later, alongside the Night Shift, he battled the [[West Coast Avengers]].<ref>''West Coast Avengers'' Vol. 2 #40</ref> Alongside the Night Shift, the second [[Hangman (Marvel Comics)#Jason Roland|Hangman]], and [[Satannish]], he battled the Avengers West Coast; his abilities had been enhanced by Satannish's black magic.<ref>''Avengers West Coast'' #76-79</ref>\n\nThe Needle was later defeated by [[Armory (comics)|Armory]].<ref>''Avengers: The Initiative Annual'' #1/2</ref>\n\nNeedle appears with the Night Shift, as part of the [[Hood (comics)|Hood]]'s gang. They battle the [[Midnight Sons]], and Needle impales [[Daimon Hellstrom]] with his needle, before [[Jennifer Kale]] knocks him off with a spell. He and the Night Shift are killed when the zombie virus mutates and becomes airborne.<ref>''Marvel Zombies 4'' #2</ref> The virus cloud begins to rain blood, and reanimates the Night Shift as zombies.<ref>''Marvel Zombies 4'' #3</ref> [[Dormammu]] assumes control of the Night Shift and uses them to fight the Midnight Sons. When [[Jennifer Kale]] and the [[Black Talon (comics)|Black Talon]] contain the virus within the [[Zombie (comics)|Zombie]] (Simon Garth), the Night Shift members are apparently restored to normal, and the Hood teleports away with them.<ref>''Marvel Zombies 4'' #4</ref>\n\n==Powers and abilities==\nNeedle has the ability to hypnotically paralyze a victim with his gaze, and is also gifted with enhanced agility and strength. The Needle is mute and mentally disturbed. He is an expert tailor.\n\nThe Needle is a fair hand-to-hand combatant, and carries a needle-like weapon over {{convert|3|ft|m}} long.\n\nFor a time, the Needle's powers were enhanced by Satannish, increasing his physical attributes to that of an athletic man, allowing his hypnotic gaze to work instantaneously, and rendering his weapon sharp enough to rend cinder block.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.marveldirectory.com/individuals/n/needle.htm The Needle's entry at the Marvel Directory]\n*{{Marvunapp|http://www.marvunapp.com/Appendix4/needlespdrwmn.htm|Needle}}\n*http://www.marvel.com/universe/Needle\n\n[[Category:Characters created by Mark Gruenwald]]\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1978]]\n[[Category:Fictional criminals]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutants]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]"}]}}}}